<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p><rs type="material">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">frieze</rs> block  (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.71</measure> x <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.345</measure> x <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.56</measure>) originally from a composite frieze, bearing i. It was later re-used; the moulding above the fasciae was cut away, and the block cut down to create a <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> moulded on three sides , chipped along the upper moulding.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p>i. <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on two fasciae. ii.  inscribed, upside down to i, on a prepared face (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.665</measure> x <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.145</measure>).</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>i: <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.045</measure>. ii: ave. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02</measure>; l.1 on moulding; ligatured ΗΝΕ, ΜΗ, ΗΝ in l.2; guidelines.</p>
</div>
